.TH aozora-flavored-markdown 1  "aozora-flavored-markdown 0.4.1" 
.SH NAME
aozora\-flavored\-markdown \- aozora\-flavored\-markdown CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBaozora\-flavored\-markdown\fR [\fB\-\-encoding\fR] [\fB\-\-strict\fR] [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR]... [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
aozora\-flavored\-markdown CLI
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-encoding\fR \fI<ENCODING>\fR [default: utf8]
Input encoding. Defaults to UTF\-8; use `sjis` for raw Aozora Bunko files
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
utf8
.IP \(bu 2
sjis
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-strict\fR
Treat any lexer/parser diagnostic as a hard error (exit 2). Default: warn and pass through
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<COLOR>\fR [default: auto]
When to colorize diagnostics: auto (TTY\-aware), always, or never
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Increase log verbosity (\-v info, \-vv debug, \-vvv trace). `RUST_LOG` overrides
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Decrease log verbosity (\-q errors only). `RUST_LOG` overrides
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: human]
Diagnostic output format: human\-readable lines, or stable JSON for tooling
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
human: Graphical diagnostics (severity, code, message, source snippet) for humans
.IP \(bu 2
json: A stable `aozora\-md.diagnostics.v1` JSON envelope for tooling
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
aozora\-flavored\-markdown\-render(1)
Render the input to HTML on stdout
.TP
aozora\-flavored\-markdown\-check(1)
Parse the input and report diagnostics without rendering
.TP
aozora\-flavored\-markdown\-completions(1)
Generate a shell completion script on stdout
.TP
aozora\-flavored\-markdown\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  aozora\-flavored\-markdown render input.md > out.html
  aozora\-flavored\-markdown render input.md \-o out.html
  cat input.md | aozora\-flavored\-markdown render \-
  aozora\-flavored\-markdown check \-\-strict \-\-format json input.md
  aozora\-flavored\-markdown completions zsh > _aozora\-flavored\-markdown
.SH VERSION
v0.4.1
